www.HillTopStudy.com
Hey all, this is a shout out to all who are interested in making extra money on the side of school, work, kids, etc. Don't worry, this company has been around since the 40's and they are stricitly confidential in agreement with all government regulations with research sites in Arizona, Ohio, Florida, New York, and in Manitoba, Canada. Some examples of fun and excellent paying studies in the past are: anti-perspirent studies, deodorant studies, nicotine patch studies, cold sore studies, tampon studies, fun & easy kids studies, oily & dry skin studies, and many more! I have seen studies that pay anywhere in between $30 to $900 (but the main ones usually run anywhere from $100 to $400). Go to that website to find out what I'm talking about or just call 1-800-874-7550 for more information!

I work for this research facility in Scottsdale, AZ and I must say that these studies are fun and an excellent income of the side of my already busy work & school schedule! Hopefully you'll click on the link above to find out for yourself about the great opportunity it is!

Lately I have been infatuated with ambigrams. I know I could never be able to create one, so I'll just leave it to the pros. For example, John Langdon who created all of the ambigrams for Dan Brown's book 'Angels & Demons'. If you come across any good ones, please tell me and/or send it to me? Thanks!
Someone from work sent these to me in my quest to find beautiful ambigrams (for those who have read 'Angels & Demons', see if you recognize the second ambigram):

energy

air

Aquarius
There's travel in your future when your tongue freezes to the back of a speeding bus
Fill that void in your pathetic life by playing Whack-A-Mole seventeen hours a day

Pisces
Try to avoid any Virgos or Leos with the Ebola virus
You are the tru Lord of the Dance, no matter what those idiots at work say

Aries
The look on your face will be priceless when you find that forty pound watermelon in your colon
Trade toothbrushes with an albino dwarf, then give a hickey to Meryl Streep

Taurus
You will never find tru happiness - what you gonna do, cry about it?
The stars predict tomorrow you'll wake up, do a bunch of stuff, and then go back to sleep

Gemini
Your birthday party will be ruined once again by your explosive flatulence
Your love life will run into trouble when your fiance hurls a javelin through your chest

Cancer
The position of Jupiter says you should spend the rest of the week face down in the mud
Try not to shove a roll of duct tape up your nose while taking your driver's test

Leo
Now is not a good time to photocopy your butt and staple it to your boss's face, oh no
Eat a bucket of tuna-flavored pudding, then wash it down with a gallon of strawberry Quik

Virgo
All Virgos are extremely friendly and intelligent - except for you
Expect a big surprise today when you wind up with your head impaled on a stick

Libra
A big promotion is just around the corner for someone much more talented that you
Laughter is the very best medicine, remember that when your appendix bursts next week

Scorpio
Get ready for an unexpected trip when you fall screaming from an open window
Work a little harder on improving your low self-esteem, you stupid freak

Sagittarius
All your friends are laughing behind your back (kill them)
Take down all those naked pictures of Ernest Borgnine you've got hanging in your den

Capricorn
The stars say that you're an exciting and wonderful person, but you know they're lying
If I were you, I's lock my doors and windows and never never never never never leave my house again

From Weird Al's "Your Horoscope for Today"


Oh and for all of those who don't know, I have my very own Pembroke Welsh Corgi now. I got him on Memorial Day. He's such a handsom lil tri color! His favorite places for sleeping are my bathroom (wedging himself in between my hamper, wall, and bath tub is always an interesting sight - the 3rd pic is proof), my bathroom (under my couch/bed thing), and underneath the end table (seriously! Just look @ the1st picture in this post!) ... I also call him my salker. Yeah, he likes to follow me around and tries to pounce my legs as I walk. >_< Yeah ... he's an interesting one. The only thing that I mainly have to really really work on is him trying to nip @ my heals when I walk. I guess this is what I get for getting a hearding dog. -.-

Yup, I'm just that good. Now tell me if this is true: ;)
Your Seduction Style: The Natural
You don't really try to seduce people... it just seems to happen.
Fun loving and free spirited, you bring out the inner child in people.
You are spontaneous, sincere, and unpretentious - a hard combo to find!
People drop their guard around you, and find themselves falling fast.
What Is Your Seduction Style?

Well, it's no really part two (You'll understand why that title after a bit of ranting). I spent practically all of the day on Saturday April 15 being the photographer for Matt & Tara's wedding (I didn't even get a peice of cake!! C'mon, I came to the wedding and took the pictures ... the least I could have gotten for payment was some cake! >(
NEways ... I got 3 bug bites while @ the park on Saturday! The major one is on the outside of my right ankle. How a bug crawled up a 4" heel without me noticing is beyond my knowledge. On Sunday it started to swell, which is of no surprise to me since I'm sensiting to bug bites. But then on Monday my ankle now looks like I'm hiding a grapfruit under my skin!!!! On top of that, I can't walk or drive my car! Yarg! Darn it being on my right ankle. >[ So now I'm taking these HUGE pills and I had to get a stupid steriod-ish thingy shot in my hip for the swelling. >.< 
I had my doctor write a note just in case I could not make it to work tomorrow. Oh boy ...

Well, maybe not as much as me but you'll get a kick out of it anyway. :)

Yeah, I got bored one day and started looking around ebay and I found this. Apparently it is a magnet. O.o

Well, I got it done! I have been wanting an industrial done for years (ever since I saw it on one of the girls I worked with at the time in Hellmark). For those of you who don't know what an industrial is, well, it is a type of piercing ... awww crap. I suck at explaining this. Screw it. I'll just show you with a picture!
My new piercing by Mr. John Vitez:

Yeah ... my ear is a little swollen right now 'cause I just got it done today (I left Divinity Tattoo @ around 5pm). Yeah ... it took him a long time to get to me. I got their @ 3:30pm (-ish) and he didn't take me till 4pm. Then, since this was the first time he had EVER done this type of piercing, it took him a lot longer to get everything aligned to where he wanted it it. I found that it only hurt when he was placing the needle-thingy on the top. Now this is where I wish he did this piercing just as fast as Tara's. C'mon! He used a 12 gauge for the piercing but the actual bar size was only a 14 gauge! I guess Dan (who John's training under) said that was best. 
... and I'll stop complaining about it and go play with Buddy-a very vocal Sheltie. -.-

Hey all! I am in a very picture taking mood as of late ... probably 'cause of my new digi. Yeah, it's just that awsome! I am also taking care of my older brother's dog, Buddy. He's a cute Sheltie ... but I do have to admit that I think my Caesar-tins is waaaaay cuter! >p C'mon, just look at my puppy icon picture thing! 'Nuff said!
N E ways ... I thought that everyone would like to see pictures of my older brother's, Brian, birthday and the Renaissance Fesitval and a picture or two of Buddy. :)
Brian & his girlfriend Ashley:

Buddy, their dog:

The Renaissance Festival (not the best picture of me, really):

And a really kewl looking mountain on the way to the Ren Fest:

Well, I was going to go to Disneyland during spring break with my Mother ... but then I found out at the Renaissance Festival that my Mom seriously was in pain. She had to walk very slow throughout the 5 hours that we were there and she couldn't step on uneven ground so pain would shoot up her spine. We were on our feet for half of the time and the rest we were sitting (at London Broil, Ded Bob Sho, and this one other one group of guys that are funny - which their name escapes me). C'mon, if she couldn't even make it for that long, she would never be able to go around Disneyland from opening (BEST time to go on rides - no lines!) til around 8 or 9 at night. So we had to cancel everything. I am going to ask to work around 38 hours during spring break. -.- My Mom is now aiming on giong to Disney around Christmas time so we'd be able to see Christmas in Disney (supposed to be really pretty when decorated). I dunno if that's going to go through or not.
On another note: I decoded against getting a printer right now and I finally decided to get an Olympus Stylus!!!! I have been drooling over them for years. Nuff said. The model that I got is an Olympus Stylus 600 ... 6.0 Megapixels CCD captures high-resolution images up to 2816 x 2112 pixels, 3x optical/5x digital/15x total zoom, and 2.5" LCD with image rotation adn histogram display. Oh, and it also uses TruePic TURBO technology. ^__^ I'm happy with my purchas. The only thing is that I have to be able to master that darn camera before Tara's wedding.
Tara's wedding: At first I was hurt because I was never really thought of to be apart of their wedding beyond just being there to watch it (hey, I've busted my but for Tara for years even when she lived in Tucson). Then I decided that my pride and my feelings would have to be kicked for feeling that. It is their wedding and it was never my place to say anything. I voluntered to be Tara's and Matt's photographer so that way I'd at least have something to do. I am also helping Tara cut out the patterns for the bridesmaids' dresses and helping her pin an everything. I suck at sewing or I would also be helping at that. >.<

Too long if you ask me ... but then again, if you ar reading this entry, you are asking me! Blehg. I'm rather bored right now. There will be no one to talk to until Dad gets home @ 9:30. -.- I might as well update everyone on my life thus far!!! (and this is where you all sigh and say "not again") Christmas was odd, to say the very least. I guess there is one plus to having your parents divorced: YOU GET TWICE THE GIFTS. My Mom got me a bunch of little stuff while my Dad bought me a bunch of expensive items like my awsome taillights, $100 to Bath & Body Works, and my Batman floormatts. Hey, my car just got 2 steps closer 2 becoming the Yellow Batmobile of Doom! That's always fun for me. To tell you the truth, beyond that, I can't really remember what else I got or even what I gave to people for Christmas. >.< I'm horrible, I know.

Then the one thing that I remember the most about my lil vacation from school was that on Sunday Jan 15 Darrell and I met up with a corgi breeder that lived in E. Mesa (the mega rich part of Mesa). They had 2 Cardigan Welsh Corgis and 4 Pembroke Welsh corgis!!!! I was so giddy that day! We spent 2 hours over at their house talking and playing with their dogs. I just wanted to take one home; they were too cute! All of their personalities were friendly and playful and they just wanted to be loved and show you that your loved too. All of them reminded me of Caesar's personality. That just goes to show you Caesar got his wonderful personality from his pa, that happened to be a Pembroke Welsh Corgi. I just home and Duane and Connie Forbs chooses me to be an owner/friend to one of their pups (hopefully if Rose is pregnant). They also refered me to several other breeders just incase. I talked to one, Lois,  that lived in Chandler, just East of the 101. We talked on the phone for 30 minutes this one night just about who we were and our interestes (which are dogs ... that was most of the convo anyway). She seems thrilled 2 meet me and I know I cannot wait to meet her. The only thing is that Darrell and I have to wait to meet her due to the fact that both of us were busy for most of the weekends in January and in the beginning of Feb. Hopefully one of these days we'll meet up with her.

Oh class @ SCC also started! I get o confused as to where everything is there. It is just to different from PVCC. I don't know which campus I like better but the one thing I do know is that I wish Prof. Birkman was still my geology prof. The instuctor for my GLG102 & 104 seems like she does not have everything together in her mind. I even found myself mentally correcting her while she was giving her lectures. Um, I guess this is where you go: darn for Harry Birkmann for teaching me correctly! I also out nerded her during my first lab. -.- We asked EVERYONE what their favorite mineral was and why. Most just named off a gemstone or looked over at her chart of minerals. Then you have me. I said that my favorite mineral was Uvarovite because the garnet group is one of my favorite groups and Uvarovite sticks out the most. I also stated that its color rivals that of an emerald. (the picture that you see below is my Uvarovite that I got last year at the Tucson Mineral & Fossil show)

Dear Santa...

Dear Santa,

This year I've been busy!

In April I pulled 's hair (-5 points). In February I put gum in 's hair (-12 points). In May I put money in 's expired parking meter (14 points). Last week I broke 's X-Box (-12 points). Last Wednesday I signed my organ donor card (28 points).

Overall, I've been nice (13 points). For Christmas I deserve a shiny red ball!

Sincerely,
ladylumen

Well, it's not really "of doom"; I just thought that sounded kewl. Some people have asked to show pictures of my Christmas tree that I decorated and but together myself. The only ornaments that I bought were my gold/ivoy Santa, gold cross, gold star, Stitch dressed as Evlis, tri-colored Corgi, and a Unicorn ornament cast in pewter then plated w/ gold (yes, real gold!) and painted. The rest Dad bought only with my approval. You see, I had a theme going on in my head of red and gold ('cause I always wanted those colors on my Christmas tree). Alas, no matter how many gold ornaments we bought, the red always seemed to over-power the gold. Oh well. I guess whenever I get my own tree (in my own place), I will have to focus more on the gold part. And you know what sucks about this tree? No matter how many ornaments we bought, the tree looks bare! Grrrrrrr ...

And a pic of Archimedes pawing at Darrell's computer screen 'cause it was moving fast:

And the il brat got into ANOTHER box to play:

At 9:30 am on Saturday morning (11/26/05) my 03 Mitsubishi Lancer OZ Rally became one step closer to becoming the "Yellow Batmobile of Doom." Why do I name it that, you ask? Well, simple, the exterior is yellow and the interior is black as well as I plan to (one I am all finished anyway) to having a large bat symbol on the hood of my car. Now you all are probably wondering what made my OZ one more step closer to turning it into it's name. Just look at the pictures and see for yourself just how sexy I made my "Yellow Batmobile of Doom."

 

17" KMC Klutch with Yokohama Parada tires ... oh yeah.

Last night I watched Stargate Atlantis for the first time . . .  And then it hit me!

Stargate SG-1 + Star Trek TNG = Stargate Atlantis

To say the very least, I fell in love with it and decided that I must have season 1 of Atlantis of DVD. Go figure that I don't have the money to guy it or complete my collection of SG-1. One of these days I tell you, oneof these days ...

and now for a picture of me and my cousin Nathan being ourselves:

Well, not really. I thought it would be funny to place that as the title since there were 5 kitties and I decided to name them after minerals to make it easier to remember and understand which one is being talked about (ex: instead of, ya know that one light tabby kitty ... it's Jasper). The people who will be bringing these very sociable kittens into their household can change their names if they want to. I just named them for easy reference. :)

Here are their cute pictures!

and now for another pic of Mama Kitty:

May I repeat myself once again: I HATE BUG BITES!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! I have 3 on my right arm, 2 on my left, 1 on my left food, 1 on my left hip, and one just under my fairy tattoo! The only reason why I dislike Darrell's house so much is because they have a crap load of bugs! His parents don't believe in spraying chemicals to kill bugs. May I say this 'cause I am an animal owner: the spray does not hurt anyone once it is dry! Believe me, just wait until that lovable bug-killing chemical dries and then it is free to be walked on even by cats and dogs (who like to lick their paws).

And for those who may be saying why in the world was I outside getting bitten. I have an excellent reason for you. Darrell and I found two 4 week old kittens without a Mama Sunday morning. We were trying to calm them down and feed them. It worked! ^__^ Here are the pics:

 

If you want one of them, they'll be ready to go in 2 weeks!

The cat that Darrell's family has been looking after just had 5 kittens on Friday! There are 2 peach tabbies, 2 whites, and one black. They will not be ready to leave their Mom until week 6. We are trying to find homes for them ahead of time so by the time that they are ready, they will be able to go to their new homes! They are just too cute! When I am able to take pictures of the little ones, I will place them up on LJ for you all! If you would like one (or two, you know how to get ahold of me and/or Darrell.
... I would just have to inform you that the black one already has dibs on it (me). I wanna call it Nightwing! Yay for the kitties!

I looked back at my summer vacation and then it hit me ... my summer vacation sucked major monkey butt! My last couple of days before classes started up again, I was doing nothing, NOTHING, but unpack boxes. I realized that I have too much crap for my own good. I wish to get rid of a bunch of it but 1) I'm not allowed to and 2) I don't want to. And the thing that sux most is that I cannot find my TI-83 ... so I just may have to buy another one ... And now I must be leafy! I'll update whenever I'm not cleaning my room! Yarg!

We started early that morning, Saturday the 23rd of July. It was humid out; it was going to be a long day by judging all what had to be done. David of course did not help at all. He sat at the table doing nothing for the first 30 minutes and then he left to go to work. If you ask me, he did not even try to ask off. If it were me, I would be like 'screw you evil people at Kolh's, I asked off for this day because I am moving and I am taking it off. It's much more important than any vacation 'cause I won't be sitting around on me bum relaxin' ... I'd be workin me tail off!' And then I wouldn't show up and have them yell at me later ... oh wait, I don't work there any more. Heh! So this is where I take a moment of silence for no longer working in retail! Woohoo!
The move was tiring, to say the very least. We returned the truck at like 6pm that day, after two truck loads full. We didn't really set up the house, and we won't be able to until the new carpet is placed in (the old one is crap and the new one will come in within the next three weeks), for new tile in the dinning room (I hate carpet where you are supposed to eat ... luckily Mom feels the same way too), and for the patio to be enclosed as an Arizona Room (yay, more space for us!). When all that is completed, maybe, just maybe, we'll have our home looking more liveable.
We sold our wall-unit and computer desk (made out of solid wood - very VERY heavy) because they were too big for the new house. Allow me to just say this: we came from a 2500 sq ft home and we downsized to a 1800 sq ft home. For David and myself, we now have 10x10 rooms (we had 12x12 before). David has to get rid of his solid wood bed (it wont fit into his room! Believe me, we tried every way possible!) and possibly the whole set that goes along with it. Me, I just am getting rid of my desk. It's too short (29" high) and possibly something smaller. I have been looking in all the places that sell desks and the only ones I like are at Office Max and at Staples. I found some that wouled match the cherry wood in my room or I could simply go with glass and metal for the desk!
Oh and on another note, we finally have a kitchen table! We were sitting on the floor or counter tops to eat our food. But not any longer! And Mom also bought an entertainment center ... so when it comes in, I will not have all the electronics in my room! Yay! I also ordered my laptop from HP! I cannot wait! We cannot set up our computer yet because we have no where to place a desk (whenever it is bought and paid for) and we have no internet! Yay for living within walking distance to PVCC to use their internet! Well ... I wouldn't actually walk to PVCC in this humid heat! I'd rather drive, even though it'll just take me  a min or two to get there. O.o
Um ... there's nothing else going on right now that I can think of ... If you want my house number and new address you know the number to my cell that rings me. :) Ta ta for now!

And mostly due to my lazyness, I haven't washed my new car and took pictures of it for all those to see. Well, now I have. Yesterday I got my car washed and waxed. It looks very pretty now. For all those who don't know what kind of car I got after selling my Nissan Xterra at the end of May ... I got a 2003 Mitsubishi Lancer OZ Rally. Very nice. :) Here are pics of it:

Now I can play at this too!

You all know the house on Greenway Lane, right? I sure you all have been over there at one point in your life. I would have to break unfortunate news to you all concering that house. I will no longer be living in it; nor will David, Mom and Caesar (The Puppy). Mom found a house off of Tatum & Jomax. I found nothing geologically wrong with the house, like I did all the others, except for the back wall in the the backyard - I found evidence of creep. I have had a lot of free time due to the fact of Kohl's cutting my hours (now I work half as many hours that I am used to arg to it all!). To give you all some clues to what I have been doing: looking up and memorizing mineral names (may I add that some are hard to pronounce as well as spell - that's double difficult!!). The ones I have gotten completely down are the minerals in the Garnet group. Garnet is not just one particular crystal - it's many with the same (more like close to) chemical composition! Uvaroite (all shades of green), Andradite (red, green, yellow, brown, black; rarely colorless), Almandite (deep red to reddish-brown, sometimes with a violet or brown hue), Pyrope (deep red to nearly black), Spessartine (brown, orange, and pink), and Grossular (colorless, white, green, yellow, pink, brown, orange and orange-red). Now that you all have had your geology nerditism (yes, I just made up that word), you can go on living your life as if I never told you about this 'cause I know none care too much about the specific name of minerals ... I know I am not interested to hear all the lovely terms in Phsycology either. >.<
